	shorttitle = {Can {Online} {Platforms} {Bridge} the {Distance} {Gap}?},
	url = {https://www.ssrn.com/abstract=4344795},
	doi = {10.2139/ssrn.4344795},
	abstract = {This paper examines the impact of geographical distance on lending behavior using data from RenRenDai, a leading P2P lending platform in China. The empirical results show that the distance between the lender and the borrower decreases the lender’s investment amount and increases the investment time interval between the lender’s investment and the loan listing being posted. Three channels behind the geographical effect are also studied: risk perception channel, information channel, and social identity channel. The topic is interesting and this paper is well written. My concerns of this paper are as follows.

(1)	Research Sample.
On page 17, a total of 294,008 lending records for 120,703 loan listings from 4,048 unique lenders in 310 cities in China were obtained, requests with incomplete information from 120,778 loan listings were dropped, and the sample used in the analysis includes 21,032 loan listings. What is the actual total number of loan listings? 120,703 or 120,778? As only 21,032 listings were used in the analysis, which only accounts for a small proportion of the total number, there might be a problem of sample selection bias. What measures do the authors take to fix this problem?

(2)	Research Design.
On page 29, in order to examine the risk perception channel, the authors regress the natural logarithm of the loan amount, lnLoanAmount, on the natural logarithm of the geographical distance. What is the point of using loan amount? Based on the argument in the first paragraph, lenders would choose to invest in loan listings with high interest rates to cover the risk of losing principle, so it makes sense to regress the natural logarithm of the loan interest on the natural logarithm of the geographical distance. However, such argument cannot be used to explain why loan amount could be used as a dependent variable. If the authors want to express that listings with small loan amount are less risker and less likely to default, supporting references should be provided.

(3)	Discussion
In the conclusion part on page 40, the authors are suggested to discuss the theoretical and practical implications of the findings. The authors should also add some contents about the limitations of this paper and future research directions.


(4)	Typos.
On page 20, the authors wrote, “We find that participants in Chinese online financing market are young, well-educated with medium income and li working experience.”, what is the meaning of “li”?
On page 31, the authors wrote, “If the lender and the borrower are from the same province, the coefficient of lnDistance is 0.064.” Do you mean, “If the lender and the borrower are not from the same province, the coefficient of lnDistance is 0.064.”?},
	language = {en},
	urldate = {2023-02-25},
	journal = {SSRN Electronic Journal},
	author = {Chen, Xiao and Guo, Gangxing (Gary)},
	year = {2023},
	file = {Chen 和 Guo - 2023 - Can Online Platforms Bridge the Distance Gap Evid.pdf:/Users/chendongyu/Zotero/storage/TEHBDK4T/Chen 和 Guo - 2023 - Can Online Platforms Bridge the Distance Gap Evid.pdf:application/pdf},
}

